file:///C/Users/hrishikeshd/Desktop/Aroonim.txt [31-07-2023 13:52:13]Once upon a time, on a warm summer day in July 2010, in a quaint little village nestled amidst green hills, there lived a  
young boy named Aroonim. He was an adventurous and curious child, always eager to explore the wonders of the world  
around him.
One fine morning, on the 15th of September 2015, as the sun rose over the horizon, Aroonim set out on his most  
exciting adventure yet. Armed with his backpack, a map, and a heart full of dreams, he embarked on a journey through  
the enchanted forest that surrounded his village. The dense trees and chirping birds filled him with a sense of wonder  
and excitement.As he ventured deeper into the woods, he stumbled upon a hidden glade on the 25th of May 2016. There, he met a  
mystical old sage named Thaddeus, who had a long white beard and twinkling blue eyes. Thaddeus sensed the boy's  
yearning for knowledge and decided to share his wisdom with Aroonim.Over the course of several months, from July 2016 to January 2017, Aroonim returned to the glade regularly to learn  
from Thaddeus. Under the sage's guidance, Aroonim discovered ancient secrets of the forest, learned about the stars, and  
delved into the history of their village.One chilly winter evening, on the 10th of December 2017, Thaddeus told Aroonim about a long-lost treasure hidden  
deep within the heart of the forest. Legend had it that this treasure held the power to grant one's deepest desires. Excited  
by the prospect of uncovering such a magical artifact, Aroonim vowed to find it.Throughout the following year, from March to November 2018, Aroonim embarked on a daring quest to locate the  
treasure. He faced numerous challenges, encountered mystical creatures, and overcame his fears. Along the way, he  
made new friends who joined him on his adventure.Finally, on the 1st of January 2019, after a year of trials and tribulations, Aroonim and his companions stumbled upon  
the hidden chamber containing the treasure. It was a magnificent sight, filled with sparkling jewels, ancient artifacts, and  
a mystical orb that radiated a powerful aura.As Aroonim approached the magical orb, he realized that he had everything he needed to be happy and fulfilled right  
there, within himself. He didn't need the treasure to grant his wishes; he had already grown so much through his journey  
and the knowledge he acquired.Filled with newfound wisdom and gratitude, Aroonim returned to the village on the 25th of July 2019, exactly nine  
years after he began his adventure. He shared his experiences and the treasure of knowledge he gained from Thaddeus  
with his fellow villagers.From that day on, Aroonim became the village's beloved storyteller, passing down the wisdom of the ages to  
generations to come. And so, as the years passed, the tale of Aroonim's adventurous spirit and the lessons he learned  
from the wise sage Thaddeus continued to inspire young hearts to seek knowledge and embrace life's marvelous  
journey.

04. Standard filters

Standard filters information

Standard Filters to avoid double count of opportunities:

Filters:

Notes

ROLE_TYPE_DISPLAY = AE



PAY_MEASURE_DISPLAY = ASV



To replicate RTB Daily (or get most recent view of the data) these are the key filters:

Filters:

Notes

SNAPSHOT_WEEK_BKT = 0



To replicate RTB Weekly most recent views, use the following filters:

Filters:

Notes

SNAPSHOT_WEEK_BKT_RTB = 0

Refer to RTB DataVerse Template (link in 'How to connect to Cubes' in Power BI users) for examples on how to apply Snapshot filters to see previous weeks or BOQ snapshots.  

BOQ is to be used to look at previous quarters only.  The current quarter has multiple weekly snapshots.

How to get Latest Pipeline (RTB Daily)

Filters:

Notes

BU = DX



Pay Measure Display = ASV



Role Type Display = AE (PS, SAM etc.)

Only one type should be selected to avoid double count

Snapshot Week BKT = 0

To get most recent (Daily) refresh select this filter = 0.  If intending to show multiple weeks in data set to <> Future Weeks

Snapshot Qtr BKT = 0

This will make setting the weekly filter easier if you'd like to review previous weeks

Close/Create/Qualification qtr

Set to the quarter you'd like to analyze

How to get Last Friday Pipeline (RTB Weekly)

Filters:

Notes

BU = DX



Pay Measure Display = ASV



Role Type Display = AE (PS, SAM etc.)

Only one type should be selected to avoid double count

Snapshot Week BKT RTB = 0

Set to <> Not RTB to avoid duplicates if intending to show multiple weeks

Snapshot Qtr BKT = 0

This will make setting the weekly filter easier if you'd like to review previous weeks

Close/Create/Qualification qtr

Set to the quarter you'd like to analyze

How to get BOQ Pipeline for a given close Quarter and snapshot quarter

Filters:

Notes

BU = DX



Pay Measure Display = ASV



Role Type Display = AE (PS, SAM etc.)

Only one type should be selected to avoid double count

Snapshot Qtr = Snapshot quarter

Set to the point in time you'd like to view.  This is not what closed or was created but what the data looked like at that time.  It needs to be used in conjuction with close qtr/create qtr/qualification qtr filter

Close/Create/Qualification qtr

Set to the quarter you'd like to analyze

05. Measures and Logic

Measures and Logic

Measure Name

Folder in DataVerse

Comments

ASV $

_Pipeline Measures

ASV to be used if needing to see Early Stage Opportunities or other Opps that fall outside traditional Pipeline

OPP #

_Pipeline Measures

Count of opportunities.  Based on SFDC OPP_ID field

OPPTY $

_Pipeline Measures

To be used in conjuction with Pay Measure fields to see specific portions of Opportunities

PIPE $

_Pipeline Measures

Pipeline Calculation.  IN_PIPELINE filter = 1 (based on GEO ADJ COMMIT = W + F + UC)

SS5+ $

_Pipeline Measures

SS5+ Calculation.  SalesStageGrp_Sort = 2 (Filter based on Opp_Stage = 5, 6, 7, or Won)

IN QTR GC QUOTA

_Quota Measures

Gross Creation Quota.  Current Quarter number only

BOOKINGS TARGET

_Target Measures

It is the sum of plan/QRF or Quota based on the target type filter

IN QTR CG TARGET

_Target Measures

Gross Creation Target full qtr number.  Current qtr only

IN QTR GC TARGET SS5

_Target Measures

Gross Creation Target for SS5 full qtr number.  Current qtr only

PIPE TARGET

_Target Measures

It is the sum of plan/QRF or Quota based on the target type filter multiplied based on the ratio.

PIPE TARGET SS5

_Target Measures

It is the sum of plan/QRF or Quota based on the target type filter for SS5+ stage pipe * target ratio. (Based on the pan number file- past 5 qtr close ratio analysis)

Close Ratio

_Pipeline Measures

Its the sum of the Won pipeline which is present in Week 1 divided by total week 1 pipeline

Projected Close Ratio

_Pipeline Measures

Its the sum of the WFCU Oppty divided by total week 1 pipeline

Close Rate

_Pipeline Measures

BOQ S3+ Flag = If(AND(RELATED('Snapshot Quarter'[SNAPSHOT_WEEK_NUMBER]) = "W1", Pipeline[SALES_STAGE_ID] in {1,2,3,4,5,6}) = TRUE(), 1,0)

SS3+ Coverage

_Target Measures

It is pipe $ divided by Pipe Target $

SS5+ Coverage

_Target Measures

It is pipe $ divided by Pipe Target $ for SS5+ pipeline
